PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776819790
OL,3,CStarmer to face PMQs amid pressure
OL,4,Cover Mandelson vetting scandal
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Dame Emily Thornberry
OL,7,Fsuggested she could bring Sir Keir's
OL,8,Fformer chief of staff, Morgan
OL,9,FMcSweeney, before the Foreign Affairs
OL,10,FCommittee.
OL,12,FThe senior Labour MP, who chairs the
OL,13,Fcommittee, was asked by LBC if she
OL,14,Fwould ask the long-time Mandelson ally
OL,15,Fto appear and responded: "I am going
OL,16,Fto invite some other witnesses. It
OL,17,Fwould probably be best if they heard
OL,18,Fthat first from me rather than from
OL,19,Fyou."
OL,26,@wD@ZOU{D@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776819790
OL,3,CStarmer to face PMQs amid pressure
OL,4,Cover Mandelson vetting scandal
OL,6,FTory leader Kemi Badenoch and the SNP
OL,7,Fhave called for Labour to hold a vote
OL,8,Fof no confidence in Sir Keir.
OL,10,FAnd a leak inquiry is under way over
OL,11,Fthe story being given to media, Chief
OL,12,FSecretary to the Prime Minister Darren
OL,13,FJones confirmed.
OL,15,FSir Olly had called it a "grievous
OL,16,Fbreach of national security" that
OL,17,Finformation was given to The Guardian
OL,18,Fafter the Cabinet Office briefed
OL,19,FNumber 10 on the matter.
OL,26,@wD@ZOUxD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776819790
OL,3,CStarmer to face PMQs amid pressure
OL,4,Cover Mandelson vetting scandal
OL,6,FChancellor Rachel Reeves backed the
OL,7,Fdecision to sack Sir Olly, telling an
OL,8,Fevent that whether Lord Mandelson had
OL,9,Fpassed vetting or not was "crucial
OL,10,Finformation" that the mandarin should
OL,11,Fhave told the Prime Minister.
OL,13,FShe insisted there is "no Labour
OL,14,Fleadership contest" when asked about
OL,15,Fthe possibility of challengers to Sir
OL,16,FKeir's authority.
OL,26,@qD@[OUrD@LO]uD@WOUvD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776819790
OL,3,CStarmer to face PMQs amid pressure
OL,4,Cover Mandelson vetting scandal
OL,6,FAt the same event, former deputy prime
OL,7,Fminister Angela Rayner said Labour
OL,8,Fshould take "bold action" to show
OL,9,Fpeople how they are tackling the
OL,10,Fcrisis surrounding the Iran war.
OL,12,FThough media reports have suggested Ms
OL,13,FRayner recently met Greater Manchester
OL,14,FMayor Andy Burnham amid rumblings of a
OL,15,Fleadership challenge, sources close to
OL,16,FMs Rayner suggested her speech
OL,17,Fsignalled she was open to a return to
OL,18,Fserving as a minister in Sir Keir's
OL,19,FGovernment.
OL,26,@pD@MOUpD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776819790
OL,3,CStarmer to face PMQs amid pressure
OL,4,Cover Mandelson vetting scandal
OL,6,FEnergy Secretary Ed Miliband earlier
OL,7,Fsaid he had feared Lord Mandelson's
OL,8,Fappointment would "blow up" and had
OL,9,Fspoken to then-foreign secretary David
OL,10,FLammy about his concerns.
OL,12,FBut the former Labour leader said he
OL,13,Fdid not think Sir Keir should resign
OL,14,Fover his decision to appoint Lord
OL,15,FMandelson to the post.
OL,26,@pD@SOUpD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
